  "english": [
    "the owner of the wheat field may <b>tell</b> the owner of the vineyard to <b>repair</b> the breach before the vines intermingle with the grain and cause it to become forbidden. If the partition <b>broke open</b> again, he may again <b>tell him</b> to <b>repair</b> it. If the owner of the vineyard <b>abandoned</b> the partition <b>and did not repair it, he has rendered</b> the grain <b>forbidden, and is obligated</b> to pay <b>restitution</b> for <b>it.</b> This demonstrates that one is liable to pay damages even if he did not perform any action at all, and consequently proves that Rabbi Meir rules there is liability for damage caused by indirect action.",
    "<strong>MISHNA:</strong> In the case of <b>one who gives wool to a dyer and it was burned in the cauldron</b> during the dyeing process, thereby completely ruining the wool so that there is no enhancement, only loss, the dyer <b>gives</b> the owner <b>the value of his wool.</b> If he <b>dyed it unattractively [<i>ka’ur</i>]</b> so that the dye is not absorbed well by the wool, <b>if the enhancement,</b> i.e., the amount that the value of the wool has increased by being dyed, <b>exceeds the</b> dyer’s <b>expenses,</b> the owner of the wool <b>gives</b> the dyer <b>the expenses. And if the expenses exceed the enhancement, he gives him</b> the value of <b>the enhancement.</b>",
    "If the owner gave wool to a dyer <b>to dye</b> it <b>red for him and</b> instead <b>he dyed it black,</b> or to dye it <b>black and he dyed it red, Rabbi Meir says:</b> The dyer <b>gives</b> the owner of the wool <b>the value of his wool. Rabbi Yehuda says:</b> Here too, <b>if</b> the value of <b>the enhancement exceeds the</b> dyer’s <b>expenses,</b> the owner of the wool <b>gives</b> the dyer <b>the expenses. And if the expenses exceed the enhancement, he gives him</b> the value of <b>the enhancement.</b>",
    "<strong>GEMARA:</strong> The Gemara clarifies: <b>What</b> does the mishna mean by <b>unattractively? Rav Naḥman said</b> that <b>Rabba bar bar Ḥana said: <i>Kelabus</i>.</b> The Gemara asks: <b>What</b> does <b><i>kelabus</i></b> mean? <b>Rabba bar Shmuel said:</b>"
  ],
  "gemara": [
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אוֹמֵר לוֹ ״גְּדוֹר״. נִפְרְצָה – אוֹמֵר לוֹ ״גְּדוֹר״, נִתְיָיאֵשׁ",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מִמֶּנָּה וְלֹא גְּדָרָהּ – הֲרֵי זֶה קִידֵּשׁ, וְחַיָּיב בְּאַחְרָיוּתוֹ.",
      "segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</big></strong> הַנּוֹתֵן צֶמֶר לַצַבָּע, וְהִקְדִּיחוֹ יוֹרָה –",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "נוֹתֵן לוֹ דְּמֵי צַמְרוֹ. צְבָעוֹ כָּאוּר – אִם הַשֶּׁבַח יָתֵר",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "עַל הַיְּצִיאָה, נוֹתֵן לוֹ אֶת הַיְּצִיאָה; וְאִם הַיְּצִיאָה",
      "segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "יְתֵירָה עַל הַשֶּׁבַח, נוֹתֵן לוֹ אֶת הַשֶּׁבַח. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>לִצְבּוֹעַ",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "לוֹ אָדוֹם וּצְבָעוֹ שָׁחוֹר, שָׁחוֹר וּצְבָעוֹ אָדוֹם – רַבִּי",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "מֵאִיר אוֹמֵר: נוֹתֵן לוֹ דְּמֵי צַמְרוֹ. רַבִּי יְהוּדָה אוֹמֵר:",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "אִם הַשֶּׁבַח יָתֵר עַל הַיְּצִיאָה – נוֹתֵן לוֹ אֶת הַיְּצִיאָה,",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "וְאִם הַיְּצִיאָה יְתֵירָה עַל הַשֶּׁבַח – נוֹתֵן לוֹ אֶת הַשֶּׁבַח.",
      "segment_ids": [
        2
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span><big><strong>גְּמָ׳</big></strong> מַאי ״כָּאוּר״? אָמַר רַב נַחְמָן אָמַר רַבָּה בַּר בַּר",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    },
    {
      "right": "275px",
      "width": "380px",
      "text": "חָנָה: כַּלְבּוֹס. מַאי כַּלְבּוֹס? אָמַר רַבָּה בַּר שְׁמוּאֵל:",
      "segment_ids": [
        3
      ]
    }
  ],
  "rashi": [
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>״גְּדוֹר״</b> שלא יוסיף התבואה אחד ממאתים בעוד המחיצה פרוצה",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:1:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ותאסר: <b>נִתְיָיאֵשׁ וְלֹא גְּדָרָהּ</b> ובתוך כך הוציא הזרע אחד מן",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:1:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "המאתים שהיו בה בהיתר: <b>הֲרֵי זֶה קִידֵּשׁ</b> ואין בטל אלא באחד",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:1:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "450px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "ומאתים וכאן יש קצ\"ט מן ההיתר וחד באיסור: <b>מַתְנִי׳ <span class=\"dh-divergent\">והקדיחו</span></b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "<b>יוֹרָה</b> שרפתו יורה שהרתיחו יותר",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:1",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "מדאי: <b>נוֹתֵן לוֹ דְּמֵי צַמְרוֹ.</b> והכא ליכא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שבחא כלל דהא נשרף לגמרי וליכא",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:2",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "למימר אם השבח יותר: <b>צְבָעוֹ כָּאוּר.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "כמו כעור בגמ' מפרש שצבעו בשירי",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "צבע ומזיק בכוונה הוא לפיכך ידו על",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:3",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "התחתונה דברי הכל: <b><span class=\"dh-divergent\">ואם</span> הַשֶּׁבַח.</b>",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:4",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "שהשביח הצמר יתר על היציאה של",
      "source_ref": "Rashi on Bava Kamma 100b:2:4",
      "gemara_segment_ids": [
        1
      ]
    },
    {
      "width": "250px",
      "right": "",
      "left": "0px",
      "text": "צבע: <b>נוֹתֵן לוֹ.</b> לצבע את היציאה ולא",
